==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misplace
<hw>Mis*place"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Misplaced</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Misplacing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To put in a wrong place; to set or place on an improper or unworthy
object; <as>as, he <ex>misplaced</ex> his confidence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To place in a location that one does not recall; to
mislay; to lose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misplacement</ent>⟦br⟧
